TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 

Suppose \[f(x) =  \frac{7x-29}{x^2+2x-15}.\]

$BR 
Then

\[f(x) = \frac{A}{x-3} + \frac{B}{x+5}\]
where



A =  \{ ans_rule(10) \} and 
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(-1));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
B =  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(8));



SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Since
\[ \frac{A}{x-3} + \frac{B}{x+5} = \frac{A(x+5)+B(x-3)}{(x-3)(x+5)}\]
and
\[(x-3)(x+5) = x^2+2x-15\]
we must have
\[A(x+5)+B(x-3) = 7x-29\]
for all real numbers \(x\).  Setting \(x=-5\) gives
\(-8B = -64\) or 
\[B=8.\]
Setting \(x= 3\) gives 
\(8A = -8\)
or 
\[A=-1.\]
EOT


